description:
Francine starts to examine exactly who she is and what she wants from life with Katchoo. She goes for a job interview and somehow nails it. Her confidence takes a knock as she tries to fit into the workplace.
                                                                                                                               
David agrees to be Katchoo's model to get more time with her.
name: A Beautiful Day

description:
Francine decides to take action about her body shape and finds working out before work is not such a great idea.  An accident on the way to work ruins Francine's outfit and is forced to wear something from a commercial shoot at work with unexpected results. 

Katchoo sees too much of his sister in David and reveals the meaning behind her rose tattoo.
name: She Has Reasons

description:
Francine's outfit is a big hit with the director of a condom commercial and is thrust into the limelight.  At home she is still having trouble coming to terms with her love of Katchoo and symbolically locks herself in a closet. 

Rachael and Chuck's relationship is put into more focus and a shocking truth is revealed. 

David confesses he is very religious and that Christianity has saved his life.
name: Dance

description: A collection of stories from Tales of Suspense that include: Tales of Suspense #49 The New Iron Man Meets the Angel, Tales of Suspense #57 Hawkeye the Marksman, and Tales of Suspense #58 In Mortal Combat with Captain America.
name: The New Iron Man Meets the Angel!

description:
Francine tries to sneak out of the apartment, not knowing how to deal with Katchoo and the kiss they nearly shared the previous night. She also finds out Rachael and Chuck are an item.  

Katchoo goes to find David and finds his sparse apartment vacated but with evidence of his feelings for her.  

Rachael shows what a ruthless manipulator she is in all aspects of her life much to Chuck and Francine's discomfort.
name: Stranger In Paradise

description:
Chuck starts to suspect theres more to Rachael than he first realized when he finds a loaded gun in her bag.            
 
Katchoo is at breaking point with her life going nowhere and Francine's inability to commit.  Francine helps her to come to the notion of going and seeing David and to find out where they stand together.
 
Darcey does some damage control and reassess the direction of her business.
name: The Elephant Graveyard

description:
Rachael starts to pack her bags without a word to chuck who is bewildered and when he finally takes a stand and demands an answer Rachael breaks out the Parker Girl nose hold on him. 
 
Francine wakes in a bed without Katchoo, who is in L.A. and promptly smashes the alarm clock, which brings a smile to her face. At work she finds Rachael gone and that she wasn't the bog-wig she thoughts she was in the company.      

Katchoo recalls when in a bar in L.A. drinks her self unconscious only to be hoisted over Tambi's shoulder and carried out.  That bar is now up for lease and she walks on.
 
Francine talks to Katchoo on the phone and gives her the news about Rachael being moved by the parent company Packard-Yerr. Katchoo immediately makes the connection that it is an anagram. Francine is shocked when she works out that its 'Darcy Parker'.
name: The Very Thing That Makes Her Rich

description:
Katchoo sneaks onto the Parker estate and spies on Darcy and David. She overhears that David loves her and wants to be with her. When this enrages Darcy David asks her to leave Katchoo be if he promises to never see her again, but Darcy is in no mood for her younger brother.                                                                          
 
Tambi spots her and lays her out cold. Taking her into a room the two discuss the situation 
  
Francine goes to see Chuck to comfort him and maybe learn a bit more about when Rachael was there. She finds a rather irrational chuck and a grumpy Freddie keeping him company. Freddie tries poorly to seduce Francine who calls his bluff and Freddie fails her once again.  
  
Chuck confirms Rachael has the Parker tattoo and lets slip about the bikini and pictures he gave to Freddie to give back to her. She punches Chuck in the nose for being an idiot and threatens Freddie if he doesn't return them right away. Tambi interrogates her about her motives for leaving the Parker girls and he reason for being there now before taking her to the 43rd floor balcony and throwing her off it utterly dispassionately.
name: I Believe You

description: The Little Mermaid dreams of leaving the confines of the sea, to live life as a human and to fall in love. When she meets the one being that can grant her these wishes she must decide what her dream is truly worth' Meanwhile a na've young girl and her clingy mother yearn to dig themselves out of poverty but when Belinda intervenes, the two women must make a choice that will forever change their lives.

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales: The Little Mermaid

description: In this corner! Weighing in at 200 lbs. and wielding a microfilament whip that can cut through solid steel: the feared enforcer of the Maggia Crime Family, Blacklash! Aaaaaaaand in this corner! Weighing 500 lbs. (in armor) and defending Tony Stark's chauffeur, ex-boxer 'Happy' Hogan, the Iiiiiiiiiiron Man! Ding-ding! Leeeeeet's get ready to.... Er, we can't finish that phrase because of potential trademark violations. But it rhymes with 'grumble.'
name: The Pursuit Of Happy

description: By popular demand, Knuckles makes a triumphant return in this thrilling spin-off tale! Knuckles presses into the heart of the desert to find the sinister secrets of his hated enemy, Dr. Finitivus, but what he finds leads to a deeper mystery...and deadly danger! With Knuckles away, it's up to Vector to protect the Master Emerald from the newest threat...but who, or what, are they? It's the pulse-pounding start of the next epic story arc, and you can't afford to miss it!
name: Echoes of the Past pt 1

description: Venom has managed to defuse the thermal bomb the government has implanted in his chest and has gone AWOL... and even crazier then he's ever been! Now Agent Smith needs help with the Venom situation... And Spider-Man is the only person who can help. But is Venom truly the bad guy?
name: The Spider Strategem

description: Eddie VS Peter once again!
name: Slaughter on Fifth Avenue

description: Eddie has come to his senses, problem is Spider-Man doesn't know and Agent Smith and his government agents don't care. Now Spidey is unwittingly leading Venom into a sonic trap designed to kill him. (this issue was at one time considered the death of Venom)
name: What Counts In The End

description:
Here it comes! Find out why and how Psylocke came back to life. Find out what Jamie Braddock is up to and why he’s been popping up from place to place in the past year. Everything has been building to this. Don’t miss it! Collects UNCANNY X-MEN #472-474 and ANNUAL #1.

This TPB reprints the following issues:

The Uncanny X-Men (1963) #472-474 and Uncanny X-Men Annual (Vol. 2) #1.
name: First Foursaken

description:
The People of Gotham City... and Batman.
   When Batman pursues a criminal into the Robinson Central railway terminal, six assorted people whose lives rarely intersect with his are present in the crowds. A doughnut seller, an elderly couple, two business people and a former convict all carry on their days barely affected by this, as other events are far more important to them. Joel Mayfield learns that he has a terminal illness, Jennifer Lee meets a charming stranger, and Dionisio Viella decides to return to a life of crime.
name: Chapter One: Giants
